methods.areEqual:
Compare key (Assumed to be a String *or* a StringCompatible) with value (created by this factory).

:param key: (java.lang.CharSequence) - The key
:param value: (java.lang.String) - The value
:return: (boolean) True iff key and value are equal (according to StringCompatible's implementation).

*Overload 1*  
  :param string: (java.lang.String) - The input String
  :return: (java.lang.String) A newly allocated STRING_LIKE_TYPE with the same content as string.
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param protoString: (io.deephaven.base.string.cache.StringCompatible) - The input StringCompatible
  :return: (java.lang.String) A newly allocated STRING_LIKE_TYPE with the same content as protoString.
